narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it. Take DS. This course alone makes it worth the trouble. Unless you have a considerable background in philosophy, this course is bound to stretch your beliefs and change the way you see the world. It is an intellectual joy-ride, one that is worth every second and every turn of the page.
If you get Aaron, stay in his section. He's fantastic!

I would definitely recommend this course to another student. The class is not easy by any means, and the papers require a different type of construction and analysis than other academic essays; however, the class provides a strong survey of some of West's greatest thinkers and stokes thought-provoking and timeless questions that I am excited to keep exploring.

I would recommend Professor Norby and this class to another student. It is a wonderful overview of early philosophers and Professor NOrby does a good job trying to explain complex ideas in a short span of time.
A great overview of classical philosophy, if that floats your boat.
